Ek browser history ka kaam hai aapke Raste (Path) ko yaad rakhna. Isme teen main actions hote hain jo aapko handle karne hain:

1. Naya Page Visit Karna (visit)
Maan lijiye aap abhi google.com par hain. Aapne search kiya aur wikipedia.org par chale gaye. Browser ko ye "Link" yaad rakhna hai.

2. Peeche Jana (back)
Aap Wikipedia par bore ho gaye aur aapne "Back" button dabaya. Browser aapko wapas google.com par le jayega.

3. Aage Jana (forward)
Back jane ke baad aapko laga, "Nahi, Wikipedia hi sahi tha." Aapne "Forward" button dabaya. Browser aapko wapas Wikipedia par le gaya.


Asli Problem: "The Branching Logic"
Yahi wo point hai jahan 4 saal ka experience kaam aata hai. Sabse bada twist tab aata hai jab aap history ke beech mein se naya rasta shuru karte hain.

Example dekhiye:

Aapne visit kiya: A -> B -> C -> D (Abhi aap D par hain).

Aapne Back dabaya 2 baar: Aap ab B par hain.

Ab yahan twist hai: B par khade hokar aapne ek naya page E khol liya.

Ab kya hona chahiye? Rule ye hai ki jaise hi aapne B se E khola, purani forward history (C aur D) delete ho jani chahiye. Aapki nayi history ban jayegi: A -> B -> E.

Interviewer dekhna chahta hai ki kya aapka code/logic is C aur D ko "saaf" (clear) kar pata hai ya nahi.


#include <vector>
#include <string>
#include <algorithm>

using namespace std;

class BrowserHistory {
    vector<string> history;
    int currIndex; // Ye batayega hum abhi kaunse page par hain
    int maxIndex;  // Ye batayega ki "Forward" kahan tak ja sakte hain

public:
    BrowserHistory(string homepage) {
        history.push_back(homepage);
        currIndex = 0;
        maxIndex = 0;
    }
    
    void visit(string url) {
        currIndex++;
        // Agar humne back karke naya visit kiya hai, toh purani forward history 
        // ko overwrite karna hoga.
        if (currIndex < history.size()) {
            history[currIndex] = url;
        } else {
            history.push_back(url);
        }
        // Naya page visit karte hi forward history khatam
        maxIndex = currIndex; 
    }
    
    string back(int steps) {
        // Steps utne hi peeche ja sakte hain jitne available hain (0 index tak)
        currIndex = max(0, currIndex - steps);
        return history[currIndex];
    }
    
    string forward(int steps) {
        // Steps utne hi aage ja sakte hain jitne maxIndex tak available hain
        currIndex = min(maxIndex, currIndex + steps);
        return history[currIndex];
    }
};
